   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM 28618_1837_05_09_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1837-05-09"/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Clifton_ENK">Clifton</placeName> 9 May 1837<lb/>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
               My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria</persName>,<lb/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HoarC1">Hoare</persName> sent me your<lb/>
               enquiry for £200 more <unclear/>
               <lb/>
               Dock Stock - Originally £300<lb/>
               was bought for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MPEX1">M.P.E.</persName>; &amp; he being<lb/>
               in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#II">India</placeName> I placed <add>it</add> in the names of<lb/>
               myself &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#PalmG1">Geo Palmer</persName> fund for the<lb/>
               convenience of disposing of it again<lb/>
               if required - £200 of this stock<lb/>
               was afterwards sold to you but,<lb/>
               the cost of transfer being heavy, it<lb/>
               was not thought worth while to<lb/>
               put it into your own name, but<lb/>
               it still remains as originally<lb/>
               invested &amp; I receive the dividends<lb/>
               on the whole sum, giving you yours,<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM 28618_1837_05_09_page02.jpg"/>
               
               &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MPEX1">M. P. E.</persName> his - I could not there-<lb/>
               fore give <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HoarC1">Hoare</persName> a power to receive<lb/>
               those dividends - the larger purchase<lb/>
               made afterwards, £1000, was placed<lb/>
               at once in your own name -<lb/>
               When the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> Dock Stock<lb/>
               was bought it was considered<lb/>
               only as a temporary investment,<lb/>
               &amp; to save power of attorney was<lb/>
               placed in my name &amp; that of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#PalmG1">G Palmer</persName>
               <lb/>
               fund - where it still remains - We<lb/>
               can sign an authority to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HoarC1">Hoare</persName>
               <lb/>
               to receive the dividends on that<lb/>
               stock &amp; carry them to your <choice>
                  <orig>ac-<lb/>
                  count</orig>
                  <reg>account</reg>
               </choice>; &amp; this I will have done<lb/>
               as soon as I return to town, if<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM 28618_1837_05_09_page03.jpg"/>
               
               the Dock Company will act on<lb/>
               an order similar to the one you<lb/>
               have sent - I shall go back on<lb/>
               Monday evening next -<lb/>
               My own dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">Fanny</persName> is<lb/>
               looking miserably thin &amp; weak,<lb/>
               but is decidedly better than when<lb/>
               I was last here - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL1">Lucy</persName> has gone<lb/>
               to spend this day &amp; tomorrow at<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Bath_ENK">Bath</placeName> with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WhitX1">M<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> Whitridge</persName> -</p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>
                  Yours my dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria</persName>,<lb/>
               very sincerely<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">L. P. Wilson</persName>
               </hi>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM 28618_1837_05_09_page04.jpg"/>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName> -</addrLine>
               </address>
            </closer>
